Uni, Milt, Caviar ($40). The treasure trio from @unigallerysg - super affordable exotic and indulgent combination, freshly flown into Singapore every 2 days! 
This is as authentic it can get!

P.S. milt is fish sperm hor. Hahaha
Spent $12 on a tub of coloring, what were we thinking and what are we doing with our money? Stick to their waffles and ice cream at @hatterstreet üò£
My virgin salted egg lotus crisp at @fook.kin and.... I'm a convert! üòç
My love for oysters never dies, not even when I'm on the streets of the night market in Taipei. $10 for 5 of these HUGE JUICY GARLICKLY OYSTERS üòç
@saveursg is still serves THE top angel hair pasta of all time. üòç They even have it as a main now!
Ice a bit coarse but still the richest matcha in Singapore - @matchayasg üòçü§©ü•∞
Super affordable solid Thai food just a few doors down Dopa Dopa - @uykdsg. Quite afforable and nice leh

Everything under $100 SGD here at Taipei Fish Market, i.e. Addictions Aquatic Development!

Ate so many types of crabs at one go, but I would recommend going for the sashimi separately and just pick the combination of seafood you love, instead of the platter if you're not a crab person! Ok la this place visit once enough Liao, sounds exciting but actually pretty meh
My to go comfort food at work for just  below $10 at @salmonsamurai üòç THE SPICY SASHIMI WITH UDON is my favorite combination!

Back to our local delights, I was honestly a little doubtful about @fook.kin's roasts because after all the best always comes from the hawker stalls we're always so familiar with.

Much to my surprise, theirs were pretty good and surprisingly reasonably priced, with a nice ambience to boot. That char siew was üíØ and the salted egg lotus root chips were super addictive as well.

I'm not gonna be cliche and say they are fook kin good but, ok la really buay pai.

OMG what's this sorcery? I was actually craving for this very drink that I was so perplexed about people going crazy over. üòÖ I've been intoxicated by the brown sugar boba magic, but I WILL NOT queue 1.5h for it.

But we've tried the one over at Capitol Piazza today, quite nice leh. Oh gosh, what's happening to me!!
